    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-14T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="1135"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1135">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A European War 1939/360: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-14T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 14, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 15—12:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>903. Embassy’s 744, April 19; 777 April 26; 794, April 30; 865 May 11.<note
                        n="29" xml:id="d1135fn29">Telegrams No. 744 and No. 865 not printed.</note>
                    Lippincott and Collum, two American interned aviators who endeavored to escape
                    on their own and were apprehended by the Turk police, departed last night for
                    Cairo. With their departure all of the 37 interned American aviators have been
                    evacuated from Turkey to rejoin their units: 17 “escaped” over the past few
                    months and 20 have been released under the recent understanding with Turk
                    authorities.</p>
                <p>Please inform General Arnold.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
